job_description:
A leading Investment Bank is looking to hire a senior Quant/Strat for their equity derivatives trading desk in NY. The team specializes in the modelling of equity derivatives products involving numerical methods such as Monte Carlo, finite difference and a broad number of optimization techniques. This role is based on the trading desk, working alongside traders to develop pricing models and large-scale data modelling.

Responsibilities:
• Develop new derivatives products working closely with trading
• Develop and improve numerical methods used in the model library.
• Deliver high quality work well and on time and manage multiple projects under time pressure;
• Be an effective communicator, working closely with other teams internally to ensure deals are executed smoothly and transaction risks minimised;

Requirements
• PhD degree in Mathematics, Physics or Financial Engineering degree is essential, with a strong problem solving skills;
• Demonstrated ability to quickly adapt to new situations;
• A strong sense of personal integrity and teamwork;
• A high level of energy and a keen desire to learn new concepts;
